Accept legacy client protocols (vanilla/R1Q2/Q2PRO) in addition to Q2REPRO.

Upstream q2repro only accepts its own Q2P_PROTOCOL_Q2REPRO, so vanilla
clients (yquake2, original Q2 = wire protocol 34 = q2proto enum VANILLA)
are rejected with \"Unsupported protocol 2.\" q2proto ships full server-side
implementations for these protocols, so widening the accept-list lets them
connect. Note: the re-release game's extended content may not fully
represent over the vanilla protocol.

diff --git a/src/server/main.c b/src/server/main.c
index e2a730a..b1860e8 100644
--- a/src/server/main.c
+++ b/src/server/main.c
@@ -116,7 +116,12 @@ cvar_t  *g_features;
 
 static bool     sv_registered;
 
-static const q2proto_protocol_t q2repro_accepted_protocols[] = {Q2P_PROTOCOL_Q2REPRO};
+static const q2proto_protocol_t q2repro_accepted_protocols[] = {
+    Q2P_PROTOCOL_Q2REPRO,
+    Q2P_PROTOCOL_Q2PRO,
+    Q2P_PROTOCOL_R1Q2,
+    Q2P_PROTOCOL_VANILLA,
+};
 
 //============================================================================
 
